        <mxCell id="G1l9C9NNaOHRkDjVYpMr-83" parent="1" style="whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div&gt;Questions for lm and in general:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;1.historical orders performance - does this need to be paginated? what does it look like?&lt;div&gt;2. gwim data what&#39;s that?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;3. update holdings can we update both the lm table and historical at the same time? failure case handling ok?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;4. custodian feeds - how do they layer in to this flow (disable the manual likely? or manual trigger feed call on a product or something? )&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;5. If a product is not in lm version of pdw but it is live after the intake process - how does that work / custodian feed&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;6. Where does this live? LM page/tab?&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;services&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;ordsr service (historical)&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;ai-structured-product-service&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;product service for pdw interface&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;lifecycle manager&amp;nbsp; - holding management and holdings products data&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;lm lambda&amp;nbsp; service&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;for ch flow:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;how do you know who to show products without holdings for?&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;lm does not utilize programs. somewhere lm maps to rep ids or something&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;gwim data is not in historical orders. it is a separate db. holdings in historical map to gmiw but those are older holdings that are not sent by gwim.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;holdings by gwim are in a sepraate data bunker sent to us through sftp daily and lm has a polished version in postgres schema lifecyclemanager_gwim&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;talk to data team (logan). transactions are built from changes to the historical order table, mulitple transactions combine to make a holding.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
